|notes = 
* {{sbc|Wrath}} deals {{tip|proc damage}}, and thus will not trigger [[spell effects]].
* {{sbc|Wrath's}} on-hit damage does not apply to [[structure]]s.
* The bonus damage dealt by {{sbc|Wrath}} benefits from {{stil|life steal}}.
* {{sbc|Seething Strike}} is not blocked by {{tip|spell shield}}.
* Attacks against [[structure]]s will not grant, refresh, or affect the count of ''Phantom'' stacks.
** They will grant and refresh {{sbc|Seething Strike}} stacks.
* The final {{sbc|Seething Strike}} stack will also grant a ''Phantom'' stack, meaning it takes 6 attacks to trigger ''Phantom Hit'' for the first time.
* The {{sbc|Phantom Hit}} occurs a static delay after the basic attack was fired (independently of {{tip|melee}} or {{tip|ranged}}), and will occur even if the attack was destroyed (i.e. {{ai|Wind Wall|Yasuo}}) or {{tip|homing projectile destruction|popped}} (i.e. {{tip|untargetable|untargetability}}).
* The ''Phantom Hit'' from {{sbc|Seething Strike}} may generate stacks and trigger on abilities that applies on-attack effect. <!--Abilities that could hit multiple targets or applies multiple instances of damages only counted as single attack at same time. 
Examples: Katarina death lotus will generate a stack per tick and only hit closest target. Zeri, Yone and Yasuo Q will only generate one stack regardless number of enemy hit. Renekton or Pantheon empowered attacks is counted as separated attacks and so on.-->
** On-hit effects, such as those from single-use empowered attacks, will not benefit from ''Phantom Hit'' and will apply their effect only once. This is due to the on-hit effect itself being consumed by the initial strike and unavailable for the second.
** ''Phantom Hit'' does not interact with on-attack effects.
