* {{ii|Guinsoo's Rageblade}} stats and effects make it a useful item for when a champion wants to specialize in dealing and applying on-hit effects. It is best used by a champion that is building to use basic attacks for their main source of damage.
|oldicons = 
|trivia = 
* {{ii|Guinsoo's Rageblade}} is named after [[Steve 'Guinsoo' Feak]], one of the main creative minds behind ''[[League of Legends]]'' and creator of ''[[Defense of the Ancients: Allstars]]''.
** According to Feak, '''Guinsoo's Rageblade''' was created with {{ci|Corki}} in mind.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/0/http://na.leagueoflegends.com/board/showthread.php?p=2851828#2851828]</ref>
** It has a similar icon to the ''[[Defense of the Ancients: Allstars]]'' item Guinsoo's Scythe of Vyse, also named after Feak.
** Guinsoo is also the name of a mysterious dagger that can be found hidden on Level 1 of the 1991 D&D video game, Eye of the Beholder. Steve Feak took his name from this dagger.<ref>[https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Guinsoo]</ref> 
* '''Guinsoo's Rageblade''' was one of the last items released before the launch of ''League of Legends'' itself.
* There once existed a bug that enabled {{ci|Sion|variant = old}} to attain negative {{as|ability power}} and {{as|{{fd|2.5}} attack speed}} with '''Guinsoo's Rageblade''' alone.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/0/http://na.leagueoflegends.com/board/showthread.php?t=1506235]</ref>
* The design is mostly similar to Kratos' blades (God of War franchise), both the Blades of Chaos and the Blades of Exile.
